### TEST 1: Verify controller is registered (NO AUTH REQUIRED - Should return 200)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/admin/test

###

### TEST 2: Try to create instructor WITHOUT auth (Should return 401, NOT 404)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/instructors
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "instructor@example.com",
  "firstName": "test",
  "lastName": "test",
  "password": "String@1",
  "phoneNumber": "11111111111111"
}

###

### STEP 1: Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5000/api/authentication/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testadmin@example.com",
  "password": "Admin@123",
  "firstName": "Admin",
  "lastName": "User",
  "userName": "testadmin",
  "phoneNumber": "1234567890",
  "userRole": 1,
  "gender": 1
}

###

### STEP 2: Login with the new user
POST http://localhost:5000/api/authentication/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testadmin@example.com",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}

# Copy the token from the response above

###

### STEP 3: Fix user to Admin role (Replace YOUR_TOKEN with token from STEP 2)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/users/testadmin@example.com/fix-admin-role
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

###

### STEP 4: Login again to get fresh Admin token
POST http://localhost:5000/api/authentication/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testadmin@example.com",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}

# Copy the NEW token from the response above

###

### STEP 5: Get all instructors (test with admin token - Replace YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/admin/instructors
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN

###

### STEP 6: Create Instructor (Replace YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN with token from STEP 4)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/instructors
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "instructor1@example.com",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Instructor",
  "password": "Instructor@123",
  "phoneNumber": "9876543210"
}

###

### STEP 7: Verify instructor was created
GET http://localhost:5000/api/admin/instructors
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN

###

### TEST 3: Try creating instructor with weak password (should get 400)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/instructors
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "instructor2@example.com",
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "password": "123",
  "phoneNumber": "1111111111"
}

###

### TEST 4: Try creating instructor with duplicate email (should get 400)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/admin/instructors
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "instructor1@example.com",
  "firstName": "Duplicate",
  "lastName": "Test",
  "password": "Instructor@123",
  "phoneNumber": "5555555555"
}
